Police have confirmed that taxis are also now blocking the Samora Machel Street exit of Middelburg towards the N4.
A large number of taxis also blocked the Vandyksdrift Road from early this morning.
Police are on the scene in Samora Machel Street where tensions are simmering.
According to someone on the scene, protests erupted after a local mine contracted a cheaper transport service provider for its employees.
Motorists are advised to avoid both the Samora Machel exit as well as the Vandyksdrift road.